text: John Hickes (fl. 1380–1388), of Oxford, was an English politician and spicer. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Oxford in January 1380, October 1383, April 1384, November 1384 and February 1388.http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/hickes- john ==References== Category:14th-century births Category:Year of death missing Category:English MPs January 1380 Category:People from Oxford Category:English MPs October 1383 Category:English MPs April 1384 Category:English MPs November 1384 Category:English MPs February 1388
